{"lemma":"بُرْجِ","slug":"بُرْجِ","root":"ب.ر.ج","root_slug":"ب-ر-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2182","","n2185","n2186"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"castle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"citadel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tower","examples":[{"text":"بُرْج خَلِيفَة","english":"Burj Khalifa"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"constellation","examples":[{"text":"تَبَارَكَ الَّذِي جَعَلَ فِي السَّمَاءِ بُرُوجًا وَجَعَلَ فِيهَا سِرَاجًا وَقَمَرًا مُنِيرًا","english":"Blessed is He who has placed in the sky great stars and placed therein a [burning] lamp and luminous moon."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spire"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"asterism"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"zodiac"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sign of the zodiac"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become apparent, manifest or conspicuous, and high or elevated","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have large, beautiful eyes where the white entirely surrounds the black","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become ample in respect of eating and drinking (of one's condition)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَرِجَ (barija) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Classical Syriac ܒܘܪܓܐ (burgā), from Middle Persian [script needed] (burg), or from Ancient Greek πύργος (púrgos), ultimately from Proto-Indo-European *bʰerǵʰ- (“high”)."},"ipa":["/burd͡ʒ/","/ba.ri.d͡ʒa/","/ba.rad͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2182","headword_ar":"بَرِجَ","root":"brj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[written in the TA without the vowel-signs, but the context seems to show that it is thus, and that the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barajN","text_ar":"بَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anything)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, apparent, manifest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conspicuous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burojN","text_ar":"بُرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a certain kind of structure. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barija","text_ar":"بَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barajN","text_ar":"بَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [also signifies]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had that quality of the eye which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barajN","text_ar":"بَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained below. (M, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barija A^amoruhu","text_ar":"بَرِجَ اَمْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His state, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, became ample in respect of eating and drinking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n2185","headword_ar":"بُرْجٌ","root":"brj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[Gr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"πύργος","text_ar":"πύργος","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Golius,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tower;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an angle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukon","text_ar":"رُكْن"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) of a fortress, (S,) or of a city: (TA:) and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fortress itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) so called from its conspicuousness and construction and height: (TA: [see 1:]) or the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brj","text_ar":"برج"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strength;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraju","text_ar":"اَبْرَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a sense explained below: (Har p. 286:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwjN","text_ar":"بُرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraAjN","text_ar":"اَبْرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwjN","text_ar":"بُرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the wall of a city or fortress are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chambers"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyuwt","text_ar":"بُيُوت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towers"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"built upon the wall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such chambers"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bywt","text_ar":"بيوت"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"built upon the sides of the angles of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSor","text_ar":"قَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pavilion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palace"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] are sometimes thus called. (Lth.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buroju","text_ar":"بُرْجُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmK","text_ar":"حَمَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pigeon-turret; a pigeon-house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"being generally constructed in the form of a turret, or of a sugar-loaf;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lodging-place of pigeons:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sign of the Zodiac;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwj","text_ar":"بُرُوج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the heaven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are twelve in number;"},{"kind":"text","text":"every one having a distinct name: (TA:) the Arabs in ancient times did not know them: (Ham p. 560:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraAjN","text_ar":"اَبْرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwjN","text_ar":"بُرُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) these are meant by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buruwj","text_ar":"بُرُوج"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned in the Kur xv. 16 and xxv. 62 and lxxxv. 1: (Bd, Jel:) or in the last of these instances, (Bd,) by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brwj","text_ar":"بروج"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the heaven are meant the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mansions of the Moon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterisms"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constellations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterisms"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constellations;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Msb;) and so, accord. to Zj, in the second of the said passages of the Kur: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gates of heaven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Msb:) or, as some say, i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quSuwr","text_ar":"قُصُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pavilions"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Golius","S","K","TA","Msb","Bd","Jel"]},{"entry_id":"n2186","headword_ar":"بَرَجٌ","root":"brj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a constitution of the eye that the white entirely surrounds the black,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no part of the black being concealed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"width of the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"width of the white of the eye, and largeness of the eyeball, and beauty of the black part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clearness of the white and black parts theeeof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"width of the eye, and largeness of the eyeball:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 560:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"width of the eye with intense whiteness of the person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distance between the eyebrows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balajN","text_ar":"بَلَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goodly, elegant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pretty; beautiful of face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [so in copies of the K, and in the TA, but in the CK “and”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"splendid; conspicuous; and well known."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}